Package com.rb.biz.types.asset

Class InstrumentTypeMap<T>

java.lang.Object
com.rb.biz.types.asset.InstrumentTypeMap<T>
public class InstrumentTypeMap<T>
extends java.lang.Object
A special case of a map of InstrumentType to some value.

Unlike an RBMap, this forces you to specify values for all keys, in the sense that when you use it, if your requested instrument is not in this map, it will always throw an exception. There is no equivalent of RBMap.getOptional(Object).

      A common use case is when we store an RBMap under each instrument type, in which case we want to ensure each key appears under only one instrument type.

      This cannot be part of the builder below, because the generic class T is not guaranteed to have this notion of being able to extract a set of keys out of it. For all we know, T could be just a string. So this method has to be separate and invoked when applicable.
